dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Grudziadz, sheet L-13. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Grudziadz, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevation. With a glossary. Compiled from Germany, 1:25,000, German General Staff, 1909-33; Germany 1:100,000, German General Staff, Sheet 42, 1934; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, Sheets 34-27, 1932; 34-28, 1930; 35-27, 1928 and 35-28, 1929. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
